Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1/2%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.

Add the tagliatelle and cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Stir the @garlic{} and @mixed herbs{1%sachet} into the beef. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Mix in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, lentils, @Worcester sauce{15%g}, @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @water{100%ml}. Add a @sugar{pinch}.

Bring the mixture to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Once the Bolognese is ready, mix in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and cooked tagliatelle, adding a splash of water to loosen if needed.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the beef and lentil tagliatelle Bolognese between your bowls.

Top with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} to finish.

Enjoy!